10 years ago I held a team meeting at PayPal to watch the new Gymkhana video (pictured above) releases that morning, I’ve been obsessed with the series and @kblock43 driving ever since the first came out. Ken did so many things for Motorsports, especially bridging the general public with racing in a positive way. It didn’t seem real hearing the news yesterday, our world definitely lost a legend, and one of the most talented drivers on earth. My thoughts go out to all of his friends & family.

There was no shortage of content, carnage and so many new friends that showed us an amazing time!  Big thank you to everyone we talked to, repose our stickers on your BADASS rides!  We even got to see the overall world record get reset the last 2 days!

20 years ago I ‘officially’ started 1320Video as a company, taking a hobby that escalated quickly into something that clearly needed to be something with more substance, more meaning, and have a name attached to it, 1320Video was born!  Over the past 20 years we’ve formed one hell of a family that has come together to support the vision I had, and we’ve had a shit ton of fun with all the crazy shenanigans we’ve gotten into.  There aren’t a whole lot of “race car bucket list” items I haven’t been able to experience with the crew.  From filming the worlds best street races in the most epic locations, helping promote new races / racers / future TV stars to the epic success they are today, experiencing racing culture in other countries and sharing it with the world, meeting some of the top racers in all sorts of different styles of drag racing, and having a front row seat to ALL of the action.  And the best part… building this company with my friends who mostly started off doing it for free or basically free for months or years… it’s been one hell of a journey, a lot of it hasn’t been easy, there’s been some epic stresses, I’ve had a couple moments where I questioned it all, but today things are rocking and rolling stronger than ever, and I can’t wait to see what the next chapters bring as we keep evolving what 1320Video is. 
Thank you to everyone who has supported me and 1320Video!

The Bonneville Salt Flats SPEED WEEK Experience - I didn’t have a chance to reflect on this wild week because of weather delays, I flew directly into Colorado for a needed week off… Bonneville Speed Week is a place like no where else I’ve been.  We’ve been to races at tracks in remote locations, but this is like stepping into a different world.
Located 1.5 hours west of Salt Lake City on a (mostly :P) dry lake bed, when you venture off onto the salt it’s more like being on a different planet, everywhere you look is just pure WHITE, making for the perfect environment for photo & video shoots.  When you pair this with old school hot rod culture that invades the salt for a week in August (one of several events there) and hotrodders from all over the WORLD, it’s something you just have to experience for yourself to truly understand.
After 20+ years of street car drag racing events, I’ve become pretty bored and jaded of the same old stuff.  My favorite part of Speed Week was the excitement the vehicles at the event sparked in me, you won’t see ANYTHING similar from car to car when you are browsing these purpose built land speed vehicles.  The wildest vehicle I saw was the yellow Firebird in my pictures, it had a custom billet 5-cylinder engine with Artic Cat internals with 5 expansion chambers covering the engine, he was hoping to go over 200mph (1 mile average) and had been in the 190's already.  The only thing more original than the vehicles are their owners.  We met people from all walks of life, all different corners of the world, famous people with million dollar state of the art cars to home-garage built cars, and it didn’t matter who it was, everyone was extremely humble and easy to talk to.  There are many well known racers or people in the industry who come to Bonneville for a break from the grind and to just do “their thing” how they want to.  Fame, money, ego, all seem to be left on the asphalt.  When racers come to the salt, everyone is on a level playing field, everyone's in it for the same love of speed.  It’s very humbling to experience. 
I can’t wait to come back for the full experience racing 5 miles soon!

It’s been 12 hard days since Dad left this world after a 2 year battle with cancer, there are many hard days ahead. I’m so grateful for the time we had with him and our family preparing for the inevitable. Our family is so much stronger now than before, but with one big missing component. Hearing the amazing stories from the many people he’s impacted over his 72 years have been very heartwarming.
